For this task, I designed a 'Digital Literacy: Student Survival Guide' infographic using Canva. The objective was to create a visually engaging resource that simplifies complex concepts like data privacy and professional branding for a student audience.I utilized a minimalist design with a high-contrast blue and white color palette to ensure readability and a professional aesthetic. The infographic is structured into three key sections: a clear definition of digital literacy, a checklist for safe internet practices (the 'Rule of 3'), and a guide to maintaining a professional digital footprint.During the design process, I focused on 'information hierarchy'—using bold icons and bullet points to highlight critical safety tips while keeping the layout uncluttered. This exercise helped me practice translating technical information into an accessible visual format. The final design has been exported as a high-resolution PNG and placed in the appropriate project folder.

